body.description: The Evenflo Chase is a forward facing-harnessed car seat holding children from 22-40 pounds (height: 28-50" ) that also can be converted to a belt-positioning booster for children from 40-110 pounds (height: 43-57" ). In addition to 4 shoulder harness and 2 crotch strap positions, this seat's innovative design adjusts to fit your child's needs as they continue to grow. Accredited as a "Best Bet" by the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety, the Chase's auto adjusting belt path assists in properly positioning a vehicle lap's shoulder belt across your child's shoulder to provide optimal safety. We've designed and tested the Chase's structural integrity to withstand approximately two times the energy of the Federal Crash Test Standard. It also exceeds Evenflo's own rigorous side impact testing standards. . Your child will also appreciate that the integrated cup holders to keep their snacks and drinks secure. The soft, machine washable seat pad allows for easy cleanup of any messes. The lightweight design comes equipped with an easy to use LATCH system, including tether, for easy installation and movement between multiple vehicles. The Evenflo Chase 2-in-1 Harness Booster Car Seat for infants and toddlers is designed, engineered, tested, molded and assembled in the United States. For almost a century, Evenflo has been a leader in safety, innovation and education. The Evenflo Chase adheres to that mission in providing a convertible car seat that combines safety, comfort and ease for the ultimate value in child restraints. Never attach two lower anchor connectors to one vehicle lower anchor bar.Cleaning InstructionsDO NOT lubricate or immerse in water any part of this child restraint, unless rinsing is permittedPlastic and metal parts may be wiped clean with mild soap and water and dried with a soft cloth. Do not use abrasive cleaners or solvents.Take care not to damage any labels.The harness can be wiped clean with mild soap and water. Allow harness to air dry.Machine wash the seat pad separately in cold water, delicate cycle. Tumble dry 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.Periodically inspect and clean the restraint's crotch buckle of food, liquids, and other debris to ensure proper latching. Place the buckle in a cup of warm water and gently agitate the buckle back and forth. Press the red button several times while the buckle is in the water. Do not submerge the harness strap. To avoid damage to the buckle, do not clean the buckle with soap or detergents and do not use a lubricant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Got this for travel….
reviews.reviewText: Mainly got this for travel. So my daughter is now 3 and for airplane rides I prefer she has her own seat with her own car seat in it and she is comfortable, she plays games, watches movies, takes naps and enjoys snacks- she does all the things & we have an easy flight this way!So this year I didn’t want to bring one of our regular every day car seats they are heavy and since she is over 40 lbs I read she could use something else like that is just booster or high back booster (don’t quote me but look it up) ANYWAYS I still prefer it have a back and the idea of a 5-point harness. Whenever I found this seat it was an IMMEDIATE PURCHASE!It IS lightweight & easy to install! It’s easy to carry and buckle and she’s safe, sturdy and comfortable. I’m very pleased with this seat! We are using it as a 5-point harness car seat and since it worked so well we’ve also now been able to install it in my mothers car for her to pick up my daughter from school to help us out and it was perfect! We will be using it for a while, for all plane travel and rental car use as well as with grandma! WIN!I definitely recommend this one especially for travel and occasional use but the fact it’s convertible and grows with our babies is wonderful and we’ll be using it for a long time as long as nothing damages it at any point. Great purchase and for a great price! Thank goodness!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Space saving, lightweight, easy installation
reviews.reviewText: Before I had the car seats that transform from an infant to a toddler booster seat. If I could go back, I would not buy a carseat that transforms. 1. They're bulky, heavy, and take up and rediculous amount of room. 2. Just don't. Kids have messes, potty accidents, sickness, food etc...and they are impossible to get completely clean. We switched from a minivan to a prius- and there wasn't enough space for feet and legs. So, we looked into these carseats. The pictures attached are before and after of space- trust me- just buy the baby carseats while the babies need them, and upgrade to this booster style seat when it's time. (Me-telling myself in the past and all who will listen)These carseats are light, easy to install. They install flat onto the seat as opposed to being at an angle or a tall base and the cupholders are easy to install and remove with a single screw. As u can tell from the photos the room that was created after buying these alone is worth it. My opinion, Do it. They're affordable. Good quality. Lightweight. And space saving.
